hopobject.body: A pension scheme rxc international salary Democratic senators Mary Landrieu of Louisiana and Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota, like Grassley, previously have called for adoption-related legislation. Klobuchar said this week she plans to reintroduce a bill to "enhance post-adoption support services for families having difficulty raising their adoptive children." The bill would require the U.S. government to "improve its data collection regarding adoptions - especially those that fail - to better develop the support services."
